course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 30 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 56 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 48 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 494 mg
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/maple-mustard-salmon-57acee82d804b55e598b4568
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 425 degrees. Halve, peel, and mince the @shallot{1%unit}(peeled and minced). Finely chop the @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped), making sure to keep the leaves and stems separate. Trim the bottom inch of the @asparagus{6%ounce} and discard. Cut the remaining asparagus in half widthwise. Then thinly slice the bottom halves.

> Tender salmon is chock-full of healthy fats, honey and mustard are a sweet and tangy match made in heaven, and cooking couscous in veggie stock enhances the flavor without increasing the calories. Talk about a trifecta!

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add the shallot. Cook, tossing, for ~{1-2%minutes}, until softened. Add the dry @Israeli couscous{1/2%cup} and toss another ~{1-2%minutes}, until lightly toasted. Add 1¼ cups water and the @veggie stock concentrate{1%unit} to the pot. Bring to a boil, cover, and reduce to a simmer for ~{10-15%minutes}, until the liquid is absorbed and couscous is al dente. Add the thinly sliced asparagus bottoms to the pot for the last ~{3-5%minutes} of cooking for extra flavor.

Make the honey mustard glaze: In a #small bowl{}, stir together the @honey{1%jar} and @whole grain mustard{1%ounce}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pat the @salmon{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}. Season on all sides with salt and pepper. Place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Spread each salmon fillet with most of the glaze, reserving 1 Tablespoon for later. Toss the asparagus tops on the same baking sheet with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Roast ~{10-12%minutes}, until the salmon is just cooked through and the asparagus is tender.

Stir the parsley stems into the couscous and fluff with a #fork{}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove the baking sheet from the oven and drizzle the salmon with the reserved glaze.

Plate: Serve the honey mustard salmon on a bed of couscous pilaf alongside the roasted asparagus. Sprinkle with the parsley leaves and enjoy!